Steffen Wich’s men started the must-win return match strongly. They had lost all their first leg matches against Spanish side Iberostar Tenerife 98-73 in October and Galatasaray 91-81, Sassari 91-84 in November last year.
Kenyan international small forward Ongwae got the Bears off to a nice start after scoring a two-pointer and a lay-up for 4-0.
After the promising start, Peterson scored a couple of three-pointers before and after another two points from Ongwae for a lead of 12-6.



