This offensive thirst managed to split Galatasaray’s defence throughout the period with Bears leading 29-20 in the first quarter. 
The Bears again started the second quarter brightly with dominant rebound play, stifling defence and an inspired attack which complemented each other, to make Galatasaray several times look completely bewildered in their own half. 
Ryan Evans was on the scoresheet several times as Peterson kept counting three-pointers to open a 16-point lead at 36-20.
After an attacking sequence, the home team managed to widen the gap to 39-23 through Adama Darboe.
Galatasaray began regrouping its troops but only for a while as Bears continued to dominate both offensively and defensively. With contributions from American DeShawn Stephens and Peterson in particular, Bears enjoyed a lead of 58-39 at half-time.



