In the third period, however, the Bears showed a little less fervour than in the first two periods. Although the pace remained high, Galatasaray slowly started to find more success in their attacking play as the Bears cooled off a bit.
At one moment, when Peterson rested in the middle of the third quarter, Galatasaray scored three times in a row without any response from the Bears.
However, Peterson returned to the court to give the Bears a much-needed three-pointer for 69-51 score.
Darboe coolly converted the last shot of the period with a clean three to take the scores to 72-55 after three more points from Galatasaray.
Despite the last period of the match starting with a point from the Bears, Galatasaray's defence showed a little more teeth than before. The Bears had a long run without scoring, which resulted in their lead being cut down to 75-61 and later on to 12 points at 80-68.
Wich’s men continued to work hard and it paid off as a three-pointer each from Peterson and Ongwae got them more breathing space at 86-68.
Then, Peterson added a spectacular putback dunk which snuffed out the fighting spirit from the visitors.
Sassari leads the group with seven points from four matches. Tenerife is second with a similar number of points and matches. The Bears and Galatasaray are on seven and six points respectively after playing five matches apiece.



